posts.title: Retired General Milley CAN STILL BE COURT-MARSHALED
posts.content:
Jurisdiction of the Uniform Code of Military Justice (UCMJ):

Retired members of the armed forces are still subject to the UCMJ, as they remain in a retired status and receive pay. This means a retired general can be court-martialed for offenses committed while in service, regardless of a presidential pardon.
